1)  JIT is part of JVM itself and its main function is to improve the performance of JVM by 
    directly compiling some code which executes above a certain threshold into native instruction.  
    JIT helps JVM here by compiling currently executing byte code into machine language


    JVM is a virtual machine used in Java programming platform to execute or run Java programs.

2)  JIT stands for Just In time compilation and JVM stands for Java Virtual Machine
    
    
3) Java source code is compiled into class files, which contain bytecode.
    JIT helps JVM here by compiling currently executing byte code into machine language

